-- Crown Chairman James Packer Raises Stake in Casino Owner by $200 Million
-- B y   R o b e r t   F e n n e r
-- 2010-10-14T07:53:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/crown-chairman-james-packer-raises-stake-in-casino-owner-by-200-million.html
Crown Ltd., Australia’s largest
casino operator, said Chairman James Packer has increased his
stake in the company. Packer’s Consolidated Press Holdings
acquired 22.6 million shares on market for consideration of
A$201 million, Crown said in a stock exchange filing today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Robert Fenner at 
 rfenner@bloomberg.net  